cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD 

This paper proposes a new projection formula for training binary weight convolutional neural networks and evaluates its performance on a spoken keyword recognition task. The paper falls under the broad category of machine learning and specifically focuses on deep learning techniques for computer vision and natural language processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since the paper proposes a new optimization method for neural networks, it could also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
